                                    //- Code sample
                                    ul#cardBasicTabs.nav.nav-tabs(role='tablist')
                                        li.nav-item
                                            a#cardBasicHtmlTab.nav-link.active.mr-1(data-toggle='tab', href='#cardBasicHtml', role='tab', aria-controls='cardBasicHtml', aria-selected='true')
                                                i.fab.fa-html5.text-orange.mr-1
                                                | HTML
                                        li.nav-item
                                            a#cardBasicPugTab.nav-link(data-toggle='tab', href='#cardBasicPug', role='tab', aria-controls='cardBasicPug', aria-selected='false')
                                                img.img-pug.mr-1(src='assets/img/pug.svg')
                                                | PUG
                                    //- Tab panes
                                    .tab-content
                                        #cardBasicHtml.tab-pane.active(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='cardBasicHtmlTab')
                                            pre.language-markup
                                                code.
                                                    <script type="text/plain"><div class="card">
                                                        <div class="card-header">Basic Card Example</div>
                                                        <div class="card-body">This is an example of a basic card.</div>
                                                    </div></script>
                                        #cardBasicPug.tab-pane(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='cardBasicPugTab')
                                            pre.language-pug
                                                code.
                                                    .card
                                                        .card-header Basic Card Example
                                                        .card-body This is an example of a basic card.
                                .sbp-preview-text
                                    | The example above is a basic card with a card header and a card body. You can extend the card using any of the features included with Bootstrap. You can use utility classes to extend the look and feel of cards as well.
                                    p.mb-0.
                                        <span class="font-weight-bold">Note:</span> The card styling in SB Admin Pro looks best with a light background color due to the background color of the card header, card body, and box shadow.

